<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="497" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,522,727]" pageId="5" pageNumber="497">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,522,547]" pageId="5" pageNumber="497">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[274,501,523,547]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Heterachthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="497" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xyleus">
<emphasis box="[274,501,523,547]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="497">Heterachthes xyleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described on the basis of a female with flagellomeres not enlarged. The study of a male specimen revealed that antennae lack enlarged antennomeres III–VI, thus excluding this species from the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[229,378,595,619]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Heterachthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="497" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[229,378,595,619]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="497">Heterachthes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and placing it in 
<taxonomicName box="[606,738,595,619]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pygmodeon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="497" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[606,738,595,619]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="497">Pygmodeon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
where it was described again, now under the designation 
<emphasis box="[151,422,630,654]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="497">
<taxonomicName box="[151,418,630,654]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pygmodeon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="497" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculatum">Pygmodeon maculatum</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
